did.head: DESCRIPTIVE SUMMARY
did.physdesc: Correspondence, reports, scrapbooks, clippings, photographs, condolences, plaques.
did.repository: Division of Rare and Manuscript Collections, Cornell University Library
did.abstract: Professional files of Jerome H. Holland, including correspondence, reports, speeches, and clippings from the various organizations with which he was involved.

bioghist.head: BIOGRAPHICAL NOTE
bioghist.p: Cornell University, Class of 1939. Cornell University, M.S., 1941. Ph.D. University of Pennsylvania, 1950. President of Delaware State College, Dover (1953-1960); President of Hampton Institute, Hampton, Virginia (1960-1970); Ambassador to Sweden (1970-1973). Presidential Councillor and University Trustee, Cornell University. Chairman of the American Red Cross and Planned Parenthood; board member of several corporations, director of the New York Stock Exchange, author.

scopecontent.head: COLLECTION DESCRIPTION
scopecontent.p: Correspondence, reports, scrapbooks of clippings and correspondence, photographs, and condolences. Papers pertain to the topics of Holland's presidency at Delaware St. College and Hampton Institute, membership on several corporate boards and philanthropic and social organizations including the American Red Cross and Planned Parenthood, ambassadorship to Sweden, membership on Cornell University's Board of Trustees, personal correspondence, engagment calendars, tape recordings, books, drafts of books, clippings and publicity, biographical material, speeches, plaques, and material relating to athletics.

prefercite.head: Cite As:
prefercite.p: Jerome H. Holland papers, #2-10-2727. Division of Rare and Manuscript Collections, Cornell University Library.

arrangement.head: COLLECTION ARRANGEMENT
arrangement.p: The original folder titles used by Jerome Holland have been maintained. At the time of processing, the files were arranged alphabetically into one series.
List of plaques, medals, trophies, etc. in accession file.
